The paper discusses the use of random projection for reducing storage and computational costs in convex programming, which is a common problem in machine learning and optimization. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of sub-Gaussian distributions, randomized Hadamard and Fourier transforms, which are common in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the geometry of constraint sets, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper discusses privacy-sensitive optimization, which is a topic in data privacy (cs.DS).
